A pan-Nigerian group consisting of Nigerians living in the Diaspora, PTB4Nigeria In Diaspora, will on Saturday host the Serving Overseer, Citadel Global Community Church, Dr Tunde Bakare, to unveil ‘Project 16’ to citizens living in the Diaspora. The event themed, ‘The portrait of a new Nigeria,’ will be streamed live on Zoom and YouTube from 7pm. The convener of the event, Adebayo Adejuwon, disclosed this in a statement on Sunday, adding that ‘Project 16’ is an initiative geared towards the emergence of a new Nigeria. He said, “PTB4Nigeria In Diaspora Group will host Dr Tunde Bakare, Serving Overseer, Citadel Global Community Church, and convener, Save Nigeria Group, on Zoom on Saturday, April 9, 2022 at 7pm Nigerian time; 12pm Mountain Standard Time (United States and Canada);1pm Central Standard Time; 2pm Eastern Standard Time; 7pm (United Kingdom). “PTB4Nigeria In Diaspora Group, a Pan-Nigerian organisation consisting of Nigerian patriots and nation builders living in Diaspora, invites Nigerians in Diaspora and in Nigeria to this event as Dr Tunde Bakare will unveil ‘Project 16.’ “The initiative conceived by concerned Nigerians is a token contribution to the emergence of a new Nigeria where service is the reason for seeking public office, and where the promotion and delivery of citizens’ welfare is the rationale for government existence.”  Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com